  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "See, I can still remember that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When did your life begin to change?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the life began to change-- it's very difficult to pinpoint.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It slowly, slowly started to-- I mean Hitler came to Austria when? 1933?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I mean we-- well, we-- I shouldn't say we because I was a little child.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the nervousness and apprehension what was happening in Europe, obviously, was talked about.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Europeans as a whole used to be-- I don't know how they are now-- but they used to be a very politically debating people all around.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, they were always talking about politics.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's not like in Canada now.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe we are talking more politics here than we ever did, but before when I came to Canada, politics wasn't a very big subject here-- which I loved, by the way.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was-- the, the nervousness started to show up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people we have known have been-- and had the chance to emigrate to wherever they could , they did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My father wasn't well.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was an invalid-- not in phys-- like not a visible invalid when he was dressed, but he was not acceptable to any country in the world as an immigrant.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And therefore, in our case, that was out of the question because in 19-- now we are going to-- coming to the time when the Germans came to, to Czechoslovakia in 1939.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we knew-- like we.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I'm saying we, but I'm really saying my mother and father because my sister and me, we really didn't have anything much to say about this.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the decision was that the family is not going to get split because there were children who were being sent to England in states and everywhere.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
